# Git Commit Message Rules

- Write in English.
- Use 20 words or fewer.
- Clearly describe the change.
- Use a prefix (feat, fix, docs, refactor, chore, test).
- Use the imperative mood (e.g., "Add", "Fix", "Update").
- Write as a single sentence.
